ovember 1583":"november 1583","1583":"1583","about 1610":"omkring 1610","1560":"1560","4 April 1617":"4. april 1617","5 December 1626":"5. december 1626","1617":"1617","1626":"1626","Saint Mary And All Saints, Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England",", Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","England":"England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Wedmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Wedmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"–1626":"–1626","1560–Male":"1560–Overleden","1583–1617":"1583–1617","1610–Female":"1610–Overleden","1623–Male":"1623–Overleden","1623":"1623","30 August 1623":"30 augustus 1623","1610":"1610","November 1583":"november 1583","1583":"1583","about 1610":"circa 1610","1560":"1560","4 April 1617":"4 april 1617","5 December 1626":"5 december 1626","1617":"1617","1626":"1626","Saint Mary And All Saints, Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England",", Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","England":"England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Wedmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Wedmore, Somerset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"–1626":"–1626","1560–Male":"1560–Deceased","1583–1617":"1583–1617","1610–Female":"1610–Deceased","1623–Male":"1623–Deceased","1623":"1623","30 August 1623":"30 August 1623","1610":"1610","November 1583":"November 1583","1583":"1583","about 1610":"about 1610","1560":"1560","4 April 1617":"4 April 1617","5 December 1626":"5 December 1626","1617":"1617","1626":"1626","Saint Mary And All Saints, Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England",", Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","England":"England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Wedmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Wedmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Haynes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Hayne  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>; see   Hain  . Compare   Hains  .","English: habitational name from Haynes (Bedfordshire), which may derive from Old English <i>hagenas</i>, plural form of <i>hagen</i> ‘enclosure’.","English: in English counties bordering Wales, perhaps from the Welsh personal name <i>Einws</i> (a pet form of Welsh <i>Einion</i>) with a prosthetic <i>H-</i>; see also   Enos  . While this is linguistically possible there is no evidence yet to show that it was the origin of the surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Hains","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Monique.","English (southwestern): variant of   Haynes   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this. Compare   Hance   2 and   Hince   2.","History: Jonathan (Joseph) Haynes, born in MA, was captured in New England by the French at age twelve and taken to QC, Canada, where he married Marie Pauzé in 1712. His descendants bear various altered forms of the surname <i>Haynes</i>, such as <i>Hains</i>, <i>Hance</i>, and <i>Hince</i>."]},{"name":"Hayne","meanings":["English (Dorset): variant of   Hain  .","History: Isaac Hayne (1745–81) was an American revolutionary militia officer, executed by the British for breaking parole. He owned an ironworks and was manufacturing ammunition for the American forces when he was caught. His grandfather had emigrated from England to SC <i>c.</i> 1700."]},{"name":"Hanes","meanings":["English: variant of   Haynes  ."]},{"name":"Aynes","meanings":["English: variant of   Haynes   with loss of initial <i>H-</i>. This surname is very rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Haines","meanings":["English (southern) and Irish (Cork): variant of   Haynes  ."]},{"name":"Hain","meanings":["English: topographic name from Middle English <i>heghen</i>, a weak plural of <i>hay</i>, from Old English <i>(ge)hæg</i> ‘enclosure’, denoting someone who lived at a farm, or a habitational name from any of various places called with this word. See also   Haynes  .","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Hain</i>, <i>Heyne</i>. Like <i>Deyn</i> this may be a rhyming pet form of <i>Reynald</i> (see   Reginald  ) or other names of Norman origin beginning with <i>Rein-</i> such as <i>Reyner</i> and <i>Rainbert</i>. Alternatively, the name may be a variant of   Hagan  .","English: nickname for a wretched individual, from Middle English <i>hain(e)</i>, <i>heyne</i>, <i>hayn</i> ‘wretch, niggard’. In some cases however, it is possible that this name derives from a spelling (not a pronunciation) of <i>hi(g)ne</i> ‘servant’ (see   Hine  ), with the inverted spelling <i>-ey-</i> for <i>i</i>."]}]},{"name":"Ellan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Mainly Jewish: shortened form of the Hebrew name  <b>Elkanah</b>  ‘possessed by God’, borne in the Bible by several people, including the father of the prophet Samuel (1 Samuel 1:1)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Ellan Haynes had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Rici Haynes. She died in 1626, and was buried in Wedmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"–1626":"–1626","1560–Male":"1560–Surnud","1583–1617":"1583–1617","1610–Female":"1610–Surnud","1623–Male":"1623–Surnud","1623":"1623","30 August 1623":"30. august 1623","1610":"1610","November 1583":"november 1583","1583":"1583","about 1610":"umbes 1610","1560":"1560","4 April 1617":"4. aprill 1617","5 December 1626":"5. detsember 1626","1617":"1617","1626":"1626","Saint Mary And All Saints, Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England",", Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","England":"England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Wedmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Wedmore, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–1626":"–1626","1560–Male":"1560–Kuollut","1583–1617":"1583–1617","1610–Female":"1610–Kuollut","1623–Male":"1623–Kuollut","1623":"1623","30 August 1623":"30. elokuuta 1623","1610":"